It is not possible to select the ALARM options when the ALARM set points are lower than the RATE that the unit is exposed to. In this case, raise the ALARM set points in accordance with the previously described steps and then select the desired ALARM options.
When a nuclear weapon has been detonated, the segment may remain in the "blinking" state.

Employment

Select Rate Alarm Visual and/or Audio Indications

  • First ensure the unit is in the Rate mode.
  • Press and hold the ALARM button and then press the RATE button.
  • Release both buttons and the display will flash the set point value for the RATE ALARM.
  • You can now select AUD (audio) and/or VIS (visual) by repeatedly pressing and releasing the ALARM button.
  • It is imperative that you DO NOT change the Rate Alarm set point that has been previously set.
  • To return to RATE mode, press the RATE button.
  • If the RATE button is not pressed, the unit will return to the RATE mode within 5 seconds.
